Descriptions:
About Us
We are Sila, a next-generation battery materials company. Our mission is to power the world's transition to clean energy. To create this future, our team is building a better lithium-ion battery from the inside out today. We engineer and manufacture ground-breaking battery materials that significantly increase the energy density of batteries, while reducing their size and weight. The result? Smaller more powerful batteries that can unlock innovation in consumer devices and accelerate the mass adoption of electric cars to eliminate our dependence on fossil fuels. We're tackling one of the biggest challenges of our time every day, and together we're redefining what's possible. Are you ready to be a part of a team committed to changing the world?
Who You Are
Lead, coordinate and grow the team of Research Associates, Technicians and Supervisors that produce the synthesized materials, batteries, and analytic data we use to invent and test our products.
Effectively prioritize the operational tasks and organize the lab capabilities and capacity to maximize delivery of results to our internal customers in the different R&D, Process and Product Development functions across Sila.
Compose and execute plans for growing and improving the operations of the R&D lab facility.
Coach, mentor, develop, and support your team through consistent feedback, navigation of challenges, and celebration of wins, encouraging technical and personal growth.
Responsibilities and Duties
Oversee the safe synthesis of Sila R&D materials and the assembly of battery cells for testing purposes, ensuring output, cycle time, performance, and quality standards are consistently met;
Develop, review and communicate operation reports and dashboard to ensure safety, quality and delivery goals are met;
Foster strong relationships with all engineering functions to ensure collaborative and efficient execution of internal requests according to Sila priorities;
Collaborate with R&D Operations Engineering in driving the implementation of process improvement tools and Lean principles and methodologies, while maintaining the flexibility and agility required in a R&D environment;
Ensure a healthy and safe working environment, in compliance with federal and state regulations and through collaboration with EH&S personnel;
Assist the Head of the R&D Operations department with long-range operating goals, expansion plans and implementation of new and improved capabilities. Support developing and controlling the operating budget;
Organize the R&D Operations management structure, teams and schedules for optimal and efficient operations, leading the recruitment, hiring, and training of Research Associates and Technicians;
Identify and share training opportunities for staff to build and improve skills and enhance capabilities. Maintain the personnel certification and training records;
Continuously track personnel performance and development and conduct evaluations, handling discipline as needed and in accordance with company policies;
Hire, coach, and support talent through consistent feedback, navigation of challenges, and celebration of wins
Knowledge and Skill Requirements
Solid understanding of manufacturing best practices;
Experienced with transferring new processes and tools to manufacturing operations;
Excellent organizational and managerial skills, a great verbal and written communicator;
Collaborative and self-motivated working style, with the ability to motivate and organize multiple efforts to accomplish goals;
Proficiency in data analysis;
Experience training, leading and coaching operations personnel and team supervisors;
Degree in engineering or science and several years of industry experience in manufacturing and R&D environments, with a minimum of 5 years managing people and setting team objectives
Physical Demands and Working Conditions
Pass a respirator fit test and be able to wear respiratory protection on a daily basis
Wear personal protective equipment including, but not limited to, a lab coat, gloves, safety glasses, and steel toe safety shoes
Move items up to 50 lbs with the assistance of lift equipment and carts
Move long distances (such as from building to building) and be stationary for extended periods of time
The starting base pay for this role is between $175,000 and $250,000 at the time of posting. The actual base pay within these ranges depends on many factors, such as education, experience, and skills. Base pay is only one part of Sila's competitive Total Rewards package that can include benefits, perks, equity, and bonuses. The base pay range is subject to change and may be modified in the future
Working at Sila
We believe that building a diverse team at Sila helps us amplify our individual talents. We are an equal opportunity employer and committed to creating an inclusive environment where good ideas are free to come from anyone. We are proud to celebrate diversity and all qualified applicants are considered for employment without regard to gender, race, sexual orientation, religion, age, disability, national origin, or any other status protected by law.

