Requirements: Bachelor’s degree (U.S. or foreign equivalent) in Business Administration, Design, Computer Information Systems, Computer Science, Engineering, Human Resources Development, Industrial Psychology, Organizational Psychology, Media Communications, Mass Media and Mass Communication, Training and Development, or related field and seven (7) years of experience in job offered, or as Instructional Designer, Instructional Design Reviewer, Training and Development Specialist, Systems Analyst, Process Excellence and Change Enablement Manager, Development Executive, or related position. Employer will accept a three-year foreign bachelor’s degree or any other combination of degrees, diplomas, or professional credentials and/or experience determined to be equivalent to a bachelor’s
Employer requires at least five (5) of the following skills gained through industry experience:
Change management methodologies and models, including Prosci ADKAR (Awareness, Desire, Knowledge, Ability and Reinforcement) Model, Lewin’s Change Management Model, and Kotter’s 8-Step Change Model;
Instructional Design methodologies and models, such as Analysis, Design, Development, Implementation, and Evaluation (ADDIE), Model of Educational Technology and Instructional Design, Bloom’s Taxonomy, Gagne’s Nine Events of Instruction, or Keller’s ARCS Model of Instructional Design;
SaaS, networking & security, end-user computing, storage, public/private/hybrid cloud, client/server applications, and hardware configuration basics;
Sales enablement, sales readiness, and sales effectiveness;
Business impact analysis and assessment, and business process improvement;
Learning management and content management, digital asset management, project Management, management consulting, strategy, and resource management;
Value selling sales methodology.
